The paper deals with deep neural networks for learning functions on unordered sets, which is a topic that falls under the subfield of machine learning known as "set-based learning". The paper specifically focuses on equivariant set networks, which are a type of neural network that is designed to be invariant to permutations of the input set. This is a topic that is relevant to several subfields of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural networks (cs.NE), and natural language processing (cs.CL). However, given that the paper is primarily concerned with the theoretical properties of these networks, rather than their practical applications, it is most likely to be classified under cs.LG.
